{
  "stem": "1765.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 137.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I used to play a lot of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] solitaire when I had time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I had a deck of cards from somewhere.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I used to lay out my fortune in solitaire.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But basically, after doing these chores, I had homework.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And it was a lot of homework.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I went to the library.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was a little library in Rubtsovsk.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That's the place I loved the best.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I now volunteer for the New York Public Library once a week for four years now in one capacity, and for many, many years before that just because I feel I always will owe a debt to libraries.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And that little library in Siberia was like a beacon of light.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "It was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was warm.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "It was one room, and it had these wonderful books and a woman who gave them out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And you could be on-- on line to get a-- a translation of a novel by Charles Dickens.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I mean, I read Charles Dickens in Russian in Siberia.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "That was my social life, to go to the library, get books, bring them home, and be able to read them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But once in a while, there was a party.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] New Year's was like Christmas here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "So there-- there was a party in school, where people got together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "When I had a birthday, or my mother's birthday or something, people we knew came.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "But it wasn't socializing with my friends.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Our social life was walking to school together and coming home together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And on our free days, the children had to work for the good of the country, for the good of the fatherland, on various construction jobs.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "We carried bricks.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
